docs {
  # Execute Dataset Rows

  Trigger graph execution for dataset rows. Each row becomes an independent graph execution via Temporal. The active graph version is resolved automatically.

  ## Path Parameters
  - `graph_id`: Graph UUID

  ## Request Body
  - `row_ids` (optional): List of specific row UUIDs to execute. If omitted or null, all rows are executed.
  - `task_queue` (optional, default: "tasks_l"): Temporal task queue to use.

  ## Response (Success - 201)
  ```json
  {
    "status": true,
    "result": {
      "execution_ids": [
        "execution-uuid-1",
        "execution-uuid-2"
      ]
    }
  }
  ```

  ## Response (Error - No Active Version)
  ```json
  {
    "status": false,
    "result": "Graph version must be active to execute."
  }
  ```

  ## Notes
  - The active graph version is automatically resolved (at most 1 active version per graph)
  - Each row generates a separate graph execution (1 row = 1 execution)
  - Cell values are mapped to unconnected input port keys by column name
  - Executions run asynchronously via Temporal workflows
  - Use the execution tree endpoint to check progress
}
